  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What buyers ask about the Global Furniture Group portfolio.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1&#8209;800&#8209;835&#8209;9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll respond in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">How do Global, Teknion, OTG, and ObusForme fit together?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>All four are part of the Global Furniture Group family, but each plays a distinct role. <b>Global</b> is the flagship: chairs, desks, tables, and storage at commercial quality, widely specified across institutional and corporate environments. <b>Teknion</b> is the premium contract tier &mdash; executive suites, high-design open-plan systems, and panel-integrated workstations. <b>OTG (Offices to Go)</b> is the high-volume value line for institutional budgets &mdash; the workhorse for school boards and municipalities. <b>ObusForme</b> covers the ergonomic-specialist niche, especially back-support seating. Finish palettes and engineering standards are coordinated across the family, so mixing tiers within one project is straightforward.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do you stock GFG-family products or are they made to order?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Most GFG-family products are made to order against manufacturer lead times &mdash; typically 4&ndash;8 weeks depending on configuration and finish. Standard-finish, high-volume items (task chairs, standard-depth desks, basic lateral files) can sometimes be sourced from distributor stock for faster delivery. BBI confirms the exact lead time on every quote.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can I spec across multiple GFG tiers in one project?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; this is the typical institutional use case. Teknion for the executive offices and boardroom; Global for the open floor and shared meeting spaces; OTG for workhorse departmental seating and casegoods; ObusForme where ergonomic back-support is the priority. Brant Business Interiors consolidates the quote, design layout, delivery, and Ontario install across all tiers in a single project file.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Are GFG-family products available under OECM?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. All four brands &mdash; Global, Teknion, OTG, and ObusForme &mdash; are included in our OECM catalogue under Agreement 2025-470. Ontario institutional buyers can reference the agreement number on their purchase order and skip the tender process. We&rsquo;ll include the OECM line item on every quote.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

